The common transport (MHD) will introduce the hole in their ticketing system on Wednesday
On Wednesday, October 1, 2008, the first passengers will be included in the history of Pražský Dopravní podnik (the Prague Transport Agency) as the date when they will get into the subway, trams and buses, which, instead of having a paper ticket, will have an electronic coupon in their pocket.
At the moment, the card is accessible to almost 100 thousand people, owners of the Opencard card.
Passengers can buy a coupon for 30 days or 90 days (this one will be valid from 1 January 2009) and at the same time have it recorded on their chip map in the information points and offices of the Dopravní podnik (the Transport Agency), located in the metro stations Muzeum, Moustek, Nadraží Holesovice, Andel, Roztyly, Letnyany, Kobilisy, Rajská zahrada, Kačerov and Luka.
From yesterday, there is also the possibility to buy coupons online on the Dopravní podnik's web pages: www.dpp.cz.
More than four hundred people took advantage of the service during the morning.
Those who will start using the online store can definitively forget the tickets in the metro stations, where they had to wait for patience in long queues to get tickets in paper.
In fact, they will purchase their coupon online and will be recorded on their Opencard card in one of the thirteen Městská knikhovna (municipal libraries).
"In these contact points, there is a guy with a trained staff who will help interested people with the purchase of the internet and will also record the coupon they bought on their card," said the spokesperson of the Martin Opatrný project.
In addition to libraries, it will also be possible to record electronic cuts on Opencard in automatic distributors installed in the vestibule of several metro stations.
What do these distributors look like?
They are red, recalling the machines to compose tickets and passengers have perhaps already noticed them in the Roztyly, Budějovická, I. P. Pavlova, Florenc and Vltavská metro stations.
"Today, the city has five, but by the end of the year, there should be twenty-four," Opatrný added.
An auto will check the coupon instead of the driver
The machines that will work from tomorrow are easy to use.
Just enter the Opencard card and the coupon purchased previously will register itself on the card.
