Talk to Sleeping
Some kids talk during the night.
I am not referring to those who wake up very awake by telling us something that happened the day before, but to children who talk during their sleep.
The first time this happens can surprise you, but it really doesn't matter.
It's a blessed change of sleep called sleeploquie.
It is quite common, especially in children and adolescents.
Of course there's more than one who talks during the night.
This phenomenon may appear in a very sporadic way (once in life, for example, associated with a severe fever), or more periodically (every day, once a week, once a month ...), the day after the child remembers nothing more.
There is no single cause that determines its appearance
They are often linked to other sleep alterations such as nightmares, night terrors, night enuresis (pipi in bed) or somnambulism, but this is not always the case.
As we have said before, they can also be associated with very strong fevers, stress or overexcited situations.
Anyway, it's a little bit of a study.
The intensity with which it occurs is also very variable.
He may speak with a quiet little voice, with isolated words, murmurs or otherwise with screams, tears, long speeches...
Where sleepiloquia becomes very frequent, it would be wise to observe the child and consult a specialist to check if there is a problem that causes much anxiety and to get an explanation of the problem.
