The time limit was the opening of the markets this morning.
In late negotiations, the two candidates for the US presidential election proved to be more favourable to the agreement, but did not express their discontent that they were forced to reach this end.
Democrat Senator Barack Obama has been awarded the addition of certain provisions to the agreement, including that to enable owners to keep their home and the salary of the heads of state-rescued companies.
"When taxpayers are asked to take extraordinary measures because of the irresponsibility of some, there is nothing to be congratulated.
