The federal government will have the possibility of delaying the arrest procedures for housing related to the real estate loans concerned, as well as setting limits on the remuneration and compensation paid to the managers of the affected companies.
The architects of the plan would like to see it submitted to the vote of the House of Representatives today, and to the Senate on Wednesday.
